Russian Equity Movers: Severstal, Magnitogorsk, NLMK, Sberbank

-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 
2011-10-18T12:19:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/russian-equity-movers-severstal-magnitogorsk-nlmk-sberbank.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  dropped 0.2
percent to 1,400.27 by 3:57 p.m. in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index fell 1.7 percent to 1,403.41.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis:  OAO Severstal (CHMF RX) sank 1.6 percent to 374.40 rubles,
a second day of declines. All of the six main metals on the
London Metal Exchange dropped as economic growth slowed to a
two-year low in  China . Rival steelmakers OAO Magnitogorsk Iron &
Steel (MAGN RX) slid 1.4 percent to 14.298 rubles, while OAO
Novolipetsk Steel (NLMK RX) dropped 0.9 percent to 77.60 rubles.
The Russian depositary recepits of United Co. Rusal (RUALR RX),
the world’s biggest aluminum maker, sank 2.7 percent to 274.32
rubles.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX) and VTB Group (VTBR RX) dropped
2.7 percent and 1.1 percent, respectively. Russia’s biggest
lenders slumped as Goldman Sachs Group Inc. reported a bigger-
than-forecast loss and Moody’s Investors Service signaled that
 France ’s Aaa rating is at risk.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Nicholson in Moscow at 
